                <head>45. Summary of Conclusions of a Special Coordination Committee Meeting<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d45fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Staff Material, Office, Meetings File, Box 15, SCC Meeting
                        #143, Held 2/21/1979, 2/79. Confidential. The meeting took place in the
                        White House Situation Room. <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>
                        initialed the top of the page.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1979-02-21T16:05:00-05:00" to="1979-02-21T16:50:00-05:00">February
                            21, 1979, 4:05–4:50 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">White House</hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>Zbigniew Brzezinski (Asst to the Pres for National Security
                                Affairs)</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>Warren Christopher (Asst Sec of State)</item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HRC_1">Richard Holbrooke</persName> (Asst Sec
                                of State for <gloss target="#t_EA_1">EA</gloss> &amp; Pacific
                                Affairs)</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Treasury</hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BWM_1">Blumenthal</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Asst Sec Tony Solomon</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">
                                    <gloss target="#t_DOD_1">DOD</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BH_1">Brown</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>David McGiffert (Asst Sec of Defense)</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">
                                    <gloss target="#t_JCS_1">JCS</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>General Allen</item>
                            <item>General <persName corresp="#p_SID_1">Smith</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>David Aaron</item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_OM_2">Michel Oksenberg</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>William Odom</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">
                                    <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <item>Admiral Stansfield Turner</item>
                            <item>Robert Bowie</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">SUMMARY OF CONCLUSIONS</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The meeting received a situation report from Admiral Turner. The Chinese are
                    bringing in additional forces and the Vietnamese may be <pb facs="0199" n="170"
                        xml:id="pg_170"/> moving main force units north. The Soviets are sending a
                        <gloss target="#t_VIP_1">VIP</gloss> plane to Hanoi and two aircraft are
                    ferrying equipment. (C)</p>
                <p>Brzezinski reported on the President’s acceptance of the SCC February 19
                    recommendation on U.S. goals in the conflict, his endorsement of eight
                    additional reconnaissance flights, his approval of our U.N. activity, and his
                    decision to have <persName corresp="#p_BWM_1">Blumenthal</persName>
                        proceed.<note n="2" xml:id="d45fn2">See <ref target="#d44">Document
                        44</ref>. See also, <ref target="frus1977-80v13#d220">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1977–1980, vol. XIII, China,
                            Document 220</ref>.</note> (C)</p>
                <p>The group discussed the general situation. All agreed it would not be in our
                    interest to see China become mired in a protracted conflict. (C)</p>
                <p>The group reached the following tentative decisions:</p>
                <p>—The U.S. should now actively seek a Security Council meeting, based on the
                    favorable responses to our informal consultations thus far. Our effort should be
                    given higher visibility through briefings by Hodding Carter at State. State will
                    send a message to the U.N. on February 22 on this;<note n="3" xml:id="d45fn3"
                        >Reference is to telegram 43803 to <gloss target="#t_USUN_1">USUN</gloss>,
                        February 22. (National Archives, RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File,
                        D790082–0993) For a description of the Security Council meetings February
                        23–28, see <hi rend="italic">Yearbook of the United Nations, 1979</hi>, pp.
                        281–283.</note> its text will be cleared through the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>. (C)</p>
                <p>—<persName corresp="#p_BWM_1">Blumenthal</persName> should express both publicly
                    and privately our opposition to the conflict. His toast at his welcoming banquet
                    should be carefully crafted to indicate our displeasure with the turn of events
                    in Southeast Asia. His toast will be cleared by the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                        >NSC</gloss>. (C)</p>
                <p>—The group agreed that if <persName corresp="#p_BWM_1">Blumenthal</persName> can
                    reach a claims/assets settlement and/or establish a Joint Economic Commission,
                    he should announce these accomplishments upon his departure. Christopher thought
                    a claims/assets settlement would help on the Hill. (C)</p>
                <p>—State is sending a recommendation for additional <gloss target="#t_FMS_1"
                        >FMS</gloss> for Pakistan, Thailand, and others in the light of recent
                    events. The group endorsed this recommendation. (C)</p>
